h3#comments Comments

p Single line comments look the same as JavaScript comments and must be placed on their own line:

.row(data-control='interactive')
  .col
    pre(data-control='input-jade')
      code
        :jadesrc
          // just some paragraphs
          p foo
          p bar
  .col
    pre(data-control='output-html')
      code
        :htmlsrc
          <!-- just some paragraphs -->
          <p>foo</p>
          <p>bar</p>

p Jade also supports unbuffered comments, by simply adding a hyphen

.row(data-control='interactive')
  .col
    pre(data-control='input-jade')
      code
        :jadesrc
          //- will not output within markup
          p foo
          p bar
  .col
    pre(data-control='output-html')
      code
        :htmlsrc
          <p>foo</p>
          <p>bar</p>

h4#blockcomments Block Comments

+unstable()

p A block comment is currently legal as well:

.row(data-control='interactive')
  .col
    pre(data-control='input-jade')
      code
        :jadesrc
          body
            //
              #content
                h1 Example
  .col
    pre(data-control='output-html')
      code
        :htmlsrc
          <body>
            <!--
            <div id="content">
              <h1>Example</h1>
            </div>
            -->
          </body>

p Jade also currently has special support for conditional comments

.row(data-control='interactive')
  .col
    pre(data-control='input-jade')
      code
        :jadesrc
          head
            //if lt IE 8
              script(src='/ie-sucks.js')
  .col
    pre(data-control='output-html')
      code
        :htmlsrc
          <head>
            <!--[if lt IE 8]>
            <script src="/ie-sucks.js"></script>
            <![endif]-->
          </head>